## Decisions Made
- Single skill `shipping-pr` + single command `/skill-set:pr:ship`: keeps the surface area small; users have one verb for "ship the PR" instead of multi-step orchestration.
- CodeRabbit detection via most recent merged PR (`--limit 1`): cheaper than scanning history and acts as a recency signal — if the most recent merge had no CodeRabbit activity, the repo is treated as not currently using it.
- macOS `timeout` vs `gtimeout` auto-detection in Step 0: macOS lacks GNU coreutils by default; resolving once at start avoids per-step branches and fails fast with install guidance.
- Convergence via single signal "did fix produce a new commit?" plus `HARD_BLOCKERS` flag: replaces blocker-set diffing; the flag disambiguates "no commit because nothing to fix" (clean exit) from "no commit because fix failed" (stuck exit).
- Split SKILL.md into 3 reference files (polling.md, blocker-resolution.md, troubleshooting.md): brings SKILL.md to 168 lines (under the 200 recommended cap), keeps reference depth at one level per creating-skills guardrails.
- Add `sleep 2` buffer before reading POST_SHA: GitHub's PR view may briefly return the old headRefOid right after the resolver's push; matches the existing `mergeable == UNKNOWN` 3-second retry convention.
- Add explicit Examples section: trigger-clarity gain with minimal token cost; covers default invocation, single-cycle fail-fast, and advisory-checks-enabled cases.

## Problems Encountered
- Peer LLM review prompt initially fired against `git diff origin/main...HEAD` while the work was uncommitted — review came back empty. Resolved by re-running with prompt that explicitly listed uncommitted file paths.
- Three critical bugs surfaced by peer reviewers (PR_JSON re-fetch missing after delegated PR creation; convergence check falsely exiting 1 on a truly-clean PR; `--required-only` flag syntax mismatched between SKILL.md and ship.md). All fixed inline.
- Direct `git commit` blocked by project pre-commit hook. Resolved by routing through `/knowledge-distillery:memento-commit` instead of `/skill-set:git:pr`'s built-in commit step.

## Constraints Identified
- Bash tool's ~10-minute hard limit forces chunked CI watching at 540s with model re-entry between chunks; longer waits would lose state otherwise.
- GitHub computes `mergeable` lazily — first query after push commonly returns `UNKNOWN`, requiring a 3-second retry to disambiguate from CONFLICTING.
- GitHub `gh pr view` may return the old `headRefOid` for a brief window after a push; reading immediately produces false convergence.
- `gh pr checks --watch` blocks indefinitely on advisory checks (codecov pending, preview deploys); `--required` is the only safe default.
- CodeRabbit GitHub App can be installed at the org level without a repo-local `.coderabbit.yaml` — config-file detection misses these cases.
- Project pre-commit hook (pre-commit-memento.sh) rejects any direct `git commit`; commit operations must route through memento-commit.

